    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-11-04T16:56:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-11-04T16:56:00-05:00" n="265"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d265">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Beaupré</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-11-04T17:00:00-04:56">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 4, 1903—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>(Received 6th, 5 p.m.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">Confidential]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>I have been shown telegram from reliable source in Panama to the effect that
                    Isthmus is preparing for secession and that proclamation of independence may be
                    expected soon. The particulars carefully guarded. Reliable information hard to
                    obtain. This Government is evidently alarmed and troops are being sent to
                    Isthmus. Repeat telegrams of importance from United States consul-general. His
                    telegrams to me may be interfered with.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaupré.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
